en_229381_0	At least 14 people have been killed after gunmen opened fire inside a church in Burkina Faso.
en_229381_1	The victims were attending a service at a church in Hantoukoura, in the eastern part of the country on Sunday.
en_229381_2	The identity of the gunmen is not known and the motive is unclear.
en_229381_3	Hundreds of people have been killed in the country over the past few years, mostly by jihadist groups, sparking ethnic and religious tensions especially on the border with Mali.
en_229381_4	A statement from the regional government said that many people are injured.
